    Training a regularization tree for dsMTL_Net

    ds.MTL_Net_Train.Rd

    Training a regularization tree for dsMTL_Net

    ds.MTL_Net_Train(
  X = NULL,
  Y = NULL,
  type = "regress",
  nlambda = 10,
  lam_ratio = 0.1,
  lambda = NULL,
  C = 1,
  G = NULL,
  opts = list(init = 0, maxIter = 50, tol = 0.01, ter = 2),
  datasources = NULL,
  nDigits = 10,
  intercept = F
)

    Arguments

    X

    The design matrices of multiple cohorts

    Y

    Label vectors of multiple cohorts

    type

    regression(=regress) or classification(=classify)

    nlambda

    The length of lambda sequence

    lam_ratio

    smallest lambda / largest lambda

    lambda

    The lambda sequence

    C

    The hyper-parameter associated with network constraint term

    G

    The graph described the task relatedness

    opts

    Options controlling the optimization procedure

    datasources

    The connections of servers

    nDigits

    The number of digits rounded for each number prepared for network transmission

    intercept

    Use intercept(=TRUE) or non-intercept(=FALSE) model

    Value

    The regularization tree

    Details

    Training a regularization tree for dsMTL_Net

    Author

    Han Cao
